{
  "number": 941,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/941",
  "title": "React destroys our HTML structure by inserting a lot of divs",
  "body": "Especially on hit lists or refined lists, there are a lot of `<div>`s wrapped around `<li>` and `<a>` elements. This destroys the formatting of Bootstrap that heavily relays also on a somehow semantic HTML structure for several layout elements like lists. For example, Bootstrap uses a `.nav-list > li > a` styling that is fully destroyed by those React divs. \n\n[I've read in the docs that jQuery is supported for custom widgets](https://github.com/instantsearch/instantsearch-jQuery-widget)... \n\nIt is unclear for me how/or what exactly is different when using jQuery, is it possible to avoid React as \"renderer\" at all or only for custom widgets?\n\nThis is related to http://stackoverflow.com/a/34517968/22470\n",
